In general, the influence of λαon the prior and consequently on the posterior results is straightforward: decreasing λαfor a given model means that less prior mass is given to larger pricing errors (i.e., more shrinkage), which lowers the prior and posterior means of \documentclass{aastex} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{bm} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{pifont} \usepackage{stmaryrd} \usepackage{textcomp} \usepackage{portland,xspace} \usepackage{amsmath,amsxtra} \usepackage[OT2,OT1]{fontenc} 
